result.execSummary:
The defendant O'Brien L. Brandenburg was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. O'Brien L. Brandenburg is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • O'Brien L. Brandenburg was found guilty of Failure to Support Child (120 Days+), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(2).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant O'Brien L. Brandenburg in court in custody with attorney Jeremiah Wolfgang Meyer-O'Day.  Matthew C. Allen appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court confirms defendant's name and address & phone number.  Court advised of charges and penalties.  Defendant understands. He immediately waived extradition, he has a place to stay in Dubuque, and the case is an arrears charge.  Requests a signature bond.  Court hears Attorney Allen, feels some cash is warranted.  Meyer O'Day states the defendatn has no money and will sit in jail for the whole action.
